OL,3,CBrother of Israeli hostage on hope of
OL,4,Cbringing hostages home
OL,6,FIt was 22-year-old Guy's first
OL,7,Ffestival: Gal wanted to look after
OL,8,Fhim, as any big brother would.
OL,10,FWhen Hamas began their attack, Gal
OL,11,Furged Guy to get into his car. But Guy
OL,12,Fwas reluctant to abandon his friends,
OL,13,Fand the two brothers separated.
OL,15,FIn the ensuing chaos, as Hamas
OL,16,Fmilitants riddled festival-goers' cars
OL,17,Fwith automatic fire, Gal escaped the
OL,18,Fmassacre in which 378 people died, but
OL,19,FGuy became a hostage. So began 21
OL,20,Fmonths of agony for both.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
